        "scenario": "Dual-write in Step 2 fails on the new table but succeeds on the old column",
        "handling": "partial",
        "recommendation": "NICE-TO-HAVE: Decide on a failure strategy — should a dual-write failure on the new table fail the whole request, or log-and-continue? Recommendation: log-and-continue during dual-write phase since old column is still the source of truth, but emit a metric so drift is visible."
